properties.Name: ExperianAccountPaymentHistoryStatusType
properties.Description:
The Payment Status is whether it is current/on-time and the payment history/whether it was late previously. Examples of Payment Status:

Ex:
- Current (OK)
- No date provided (NO)
- 30 days late (30)
- 60 days late (60)
- 90 days late (90)
- 120 days late (120)
- Key derogatory (KD)
- Repossession or Foreclosure (RF)
- Payment Plan (PP
- Closed (CLS)
- Charge off (CO)
- Defaulted on contract (D)
- No data for this time period (ND)
-  Repossession (R)
-  Paid by creditor (PBC)
-  Insurance claim (IC)
-  Claim filed with government (G)
